FBIS4-42872 "drweu111_q_94006" FBIS-WEU-94-111 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 TURKEY Cuban Ambassador Urges Turkish Investment Cuban Ambassador Urges Turkish Investment TA0806144094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2100 GMT 7 Jun 94 TA0806144094 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Text] Cuban Ambassador to Ankara Jorge Castro [name and title as heard] has stated that Cuba wants to develop economic relations with Turkey and invited Turkish businessmen and industrialists to invest in his country. In a news conference in Izmir, the Cuban ambassador indicated that joint cooperation can be established with Turkey in many areas and added that for this to happen the two countries should get to know each other very well. Castro advised Turkish businessmen to take advantage of the business incentives granted to foreign investors in Cuba.
